Texas Air Corp's Eastern Airlinessubsidiary said it will cut 259 jobs for mechanics and relatedemployees in Miami and Boston, effective around May One.    The company said part of the staff cuts result from theproposed sale of five Boeing Co &lt;BA> 727-100's and two LockheedCorp &lt;LK> L-1011's, as well as the previously announcedtransfer of six &lt;Airbus Industrie> A300's to ContinentalAirlines, another Texas Air subsidiary. Reuter&#3;